    <title id="GUID-71E6E7FF-D420-465A-9CFA-86F8BA5BE094">Group Mapping</title><?oxy_comment_end?>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>This function allows users to directly register agent to a specific group via the
                StellarOne web console.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Go to <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Downloads/Updates</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select the
                        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?><uicontrol>Agent</uicontrol><?oxy_custom_end?>
                    tab.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Download</uicontrol> to download the Installer Package.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>download Group.ini</uicontrol> link.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>The <uicontrol>Select a group</uicontrol> window appears.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select a group for the target agent and click <uicontrol>Download</uicontrol>.
                    Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the window.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>A file named <filepath>Group.ini</filepath> has been downloaded. Place the
                        <filepath>Group.ini</filepath> file as the top-level file in the installer
                    package of the target agent.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Run the installation on the target agent. Make sure the agent is connected to
                    StellarOne console during the installation process.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Users can check the StellarOne console and the on-site target agent to see if
                    the agent is successfully registered.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
